Package abstractDataTypesImplemented

Class PersonUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph

java.lang.Object
abstractDataTypesImplemented.PersonUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph
All Implemented Interfaces:
GraphADT<Person>
public class PersonUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph
extends java.lang.Object
implements GraphADT<Person>
This class is an implementation of GraphADT with the type Person. It's an undirected graph using adjacency list. Uses an IntegerUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph as base and assigns each Person an ID that symbolizes a vertex in the graph.
Author:
Borja Moralejo Tobajas and Imanol Mara√±a Hurtado

    • pathAtDistance6

      public java.lang.Iterable<Person> pathAtDistance6​(Person person1, Person person2)
      Returns an Iterable Person type containing the shortest path between two people if they are at less than 6 steps. Returns null if anyone of them is not in the graph or if there wasn't a connection between them at a distance less than 6. Returns a single element if both of them are equal. The path returned is from person1 to person2
      Parameters:
      person1 - Person
      person2 - Person
      Returns:
      Iterable Person type if there's path, null if there is not
